titleproper.value: Guide to the Jill "Billy" Rainsford Papers <lb/><date calendar="gregorian" era="ce">1922-1991 </date><lb/> <num>MSS.030</num>

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2017-06-16T14:03:07</date>

abstract.value: Jill Rainsford (1905-1994) was born Marguerite Rainsford (known as Billy), in Brooklyn. She was an actress, songwriter, painter and author, and was prominent in New York's Vaudeville theater and motion picture industry during the 1920s both as an actress and songwriter. The collection includes an unpublished autobiography, correspondence, sheet music and a large number of photographs and memorabilia.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations sshould take the following form:<lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Jill "Billy" Rainsford Papers ; MSS 030; box number; folder number; <address><addressline>Fales Library and Special Collections</addressline></address>, New York University Libraries.
The Jill "Billy" Rainsford Papers were donated to New York University in 1995 by her sister Doris Rainsford of Athens, Ohio.

This series contains Bradshaw Crandall magazine and calendar covers, copies of magazines which feature Billy (1922-1923), and theatre and opera programs collected by Julia Rainsford. A briefcase which belonged to Billy is also included.
